title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1991-02-19
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Greatest Story Ever Told, Althea, Queen Jane Approximately, Ramble On Rose, Picasso Moon, Peggy-O, Cassidy, New Speedway Boogie

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Truckin'-> Crazy Fingers-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> All Along The Watchtower-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Something weird Something weird happens in Rider.  It is on other board sources too.  It is like there are 2 sources out of phase.  Totally screws it up at around 2:30 in IKYR.  
Also, Vince is up much higher on this source than the other board.  If that kind of thing matters to you.

Much better balanced than the "fixed" Miller SBD Bobby is very loud in the mix, but this is true of the AUD as well. Actually, the whole mix for the show seems rather mushy, and while it's mostly very well-played, it sounds hectic and brittle.
